document_data.History:
Cassyt was a young worshiper of Kelemvor living in Phlan, working under [[Yovir Glandon]]. However, she spent most of her time studying books instead of patrol the graveyard's catacombs. Recently, by the {{YearlinkName|1489}}, she with some adventurers were instructed by doomguide Glandon to investigate the Graveyard, where were signaled [[undead]] activities and disappearance of some Kelemvorite.{{Cite adventurers league/Dues for the Dead|7-8}} This adventure helped her grow.{{Cite adventurers league/Dues for the Dead|18-19}}

During the [[Cult of the Dragon]] coup in the city, she helped the resistance forces. She guided them through the sewers in order to get Lord Regent [[Ector Brahms]] safely out of the city.{{Cite adventurers league/Tyranny in Phlan|25-26}}

In the {{YearlinkName|1491}}, Cassyt was in [[Mulmaster]] where investigated about possible corruption of the resurrected Aleyd{{Cite adventurers league/Black Heart of Vengeance|19}} At last she tried to resonate with Aleyd but her old friend killed Cassyt on surprise{{Cite adventurers league/Black Heart of Vengeance|23}}
